BRUSSELS, Jan. 11 (Xinhua) -- European Parliament President David Sassoli died at 65 in Italy early Tuesday, his spokesperson has said. Sassoli passed away at 1:15 a.m. (0015 GMT) at a hospital in the city of Aviano, Italy, spokesperson Roberto Cuillo tweeted. On Monday, Cuillo said the well-known Italian politician had been hospitalized for more than two weeks due to a serious complication relating to immune system dysfunction. Sassoli was elected president of the European Parliament in 2019 and his term of office would have expired in days.  â– 